<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="105" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[212,330,1071,1095]" box="[212,330,1071,1095]" pageId="18" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis box="[212,330,1071,1095]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="105">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[212,1172,1111,1328]" pageId="18" pageNumber="105">
The depository of the material is not identified and we were unable to obtain specimens of this species. This species was considered to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lopes" baseAuthorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dodgei" subGenus="Bezzisca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="105">D. (B.) dodgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes HS" box="[326,487,1175,1199]" pageId="18" pageNumber="105" pagination="485 - 489" refId="ref6438" refString="Lopes HS. 1975 c. On some new species of Sarcophagidae from Costa Rica (Diptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia 35: 485 - 489." type="journal article" year="1975">Lopes (1975c)</bibRefCitation>
, who distinguished it by several unique characteristics of the male terminalia. Lopes’ illustrations do not allow for verification of the shape of the pregonite and the number of posterior keels in the basiphallus. However, it is possible to notice the lack of spines in the distiphallus. It appears that species is also similar to 
<emphasis box="[212,382,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lopes" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[212,378,1304,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" subGenus="Bezzisca">D.(B.) bicolor</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
